									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>117 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end). </p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation from folio 9 onwards, the preceding folios being flyleaves.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 4 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Much stained and slightly water-damaged (lower edges).</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="27 " writtenLines="27 ">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Titles and initial words in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso, and under every column if the page is divided.</p>
									<p>Visible vertical hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Red edges.</p>
									<p>Maniculae with additional marginal notes, e.g., folio 10r, 11v.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian cursive script of the 17th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yehoshu῾a Ḳolonyah</name>: inscribed, folio 6r.</p>
							<p>Folios 1r-8v and 117v served as flyleaves and contain scribblings, doodles and various calculations.</p>
						</additions>
